column13: Adapted from: www.predimed.es, Int J Epidemiol. 2012 Apr; 41(2):377-385, J Nutr. 2011 Jun; 141(6):1140-1145 (Nov 2017)
column20: Do you use olive oil as the main source of fat for cooking?

column13: Adapted from: www.predimed.es, Int J Epidemiol. 2012 Apr; 41(2):377-385, J Nutr. 2011 Jun; 141(6):1140-1145 (Nov 2017)
column20:
How many tablespoons of olive oil do you use each day?
Include olive oil used in salads, meals eaten away from home, frying etc

column13: Adapted from: www.predimed.es, Int J Epidemiol. 2012 Apr; 41(2):377-385, J Nutr. 2011 Jun; 141(6):1140-1145 (Nov 2017)
column20:
How many servings of vegetables do you eat per day?
One serving is ½ cup raw or cooked vegetables or 1 cup of raw salad greens

column13: Adapted from: www.predimed.es, Int J Epidemiol. 2012 Apr; 41(2):377-385, J Nutr. 2011 Jun; 141(6):1140-1145 (Nov 2017)
column20:
How many servings of whole fruit do you eat per day?
One serving is ½ cup or a medium sized piece of whole fruit

column13: Adapted from: www.predimed.es, Int J Epidemiol. 2012 Apr; 41(2):377-385, J Nutr. 2011 Jun; 141(6):1140-1145 (Nov 2017)
column20:
How many servings of red meat, hamburger or sausages do you eat per week?
One serving is 3 ½ -5 ½ ounces (100-150 grams)

column13: Adapted from: www.predimed.es, Int J Epidemiol. 2012 Apr; 41(2):377-385, J Nutr. 2011 Jun; 141(6):1140-1145 (Nov 2017)
column20:
How many servings of butter, margarine or cream do you consume per day?
One serving is 1 Tablespoon. This does not include soft non-hydrogenated margarines

column13: Adapted from: www.predimed.es, Int J Epidemiol. 2012 Apr; 41(2):377-385, J Nutr. 2011 Jun; 141(6):1140-1145 (Nov 2017)
column20:
How many sugar sweetened beverages do you drink per week?
One serving is 355ml or one can of pop or 12 ounces.
This includes any drinks with added sugars such as regular pop, fruit drinks, sports drinks, energy drinks, iced tea

column13: Adapted from: www.predimed.es, Int J Epidemiol. 2012 Apr; 41(2):377-385, J Nutr. 2011 Jun; 141(6):1140-1145 (Nov 2017)
column20:
Do you drink wine? How much do you drink per week?
1 glass = 150ml or 5 oz

column13: Adapted from: www.predimed.es, Int J Epidemiol. 2012 Apr; 41(2):377-385, J Nutr. 2011 Jun; 141(6):1140-1145 (Nov 2017)
column20:
How many servings of legumes like kidney beans, chick peas, lentils, black beans, split peas do you eat per week?
One serving is 5 ounces or 150 grams or ½ - 2/3 cup

column13: Adapted from: www.predimed.es, Int J Epidemiol. 2012 Apr; 41(2):377-385, J Nutr. 2011 Jun; 141(6):1140-1145 (Nov 2017)
column20:
How many servings of fish or seafood do you eat per week?
One serving of fish is 3 ½ -5 ½ ounces or 100-150 grams
One serving of seafood is 4-5 pieces or 7 ounces or 200 grams

column13: Adapted from: www.predimed.es, Int J Epidemiol. 2012 Apr; 41(2):377-385, J Nutr. 2011 Jun; 141(6):1140-1145 (Nov 2017)
column20: How many times do you eat baked goods such as pie, cookies, cake or doughnuts per week?

column13: Adapted from: www.predimed.es, Int J Epidemiol. 2012 Apr; 41(2):377-385, J Nutr. 2011 Jun; 141(6):1140-1145 (Nov 2017)
column20:
How many times do you eat nuts per week?
1 serving is 30 grams or 1 ounce

column13: Adapted from: www.predimed.es, Int J Epidemiol. 2012 Apr; 41(2):377-385, J Nutr. 2011 Jun; 141(6):1140-1145 (Nov 2017)
column20: Do you eat chicken or turkey more often than beef, pork, hamburger or sausage?
